John Doe is the pseudonym used by the whistleblower in the 2016 Panama Papers leak, who turned over 11.5 million documents from the law firm Mossack Fonseca to the newspaper SÃ¼ddeutsche Zeitung. On May 5, 2016, John Doe published a statement The Revolution Will Be Digitised; Doe explained he made the files public to underline growing income inequality and financial corruption globally. The whistleblower has offered to help prosecutors build their cases, on condition of legal protection.


